# Self-referential HEAP shadow: `s := s + "!"` in a nested block shadows the
# outer string `s`. The RHS reads the ENCLOSING s ("ab") and binds a fresh
# independent value ("ab!"); the outer s is untouched. Routes through the
# normal SDecl path (not the string-accumulator path -- no later `s = s + ...`).
# Expected: inner "ab!", outer still "ab".
fn main():
    s := "ab"
    if len(s) > 0:
        s := s + "!"
        print("inner " + s)
    print("outer " + s)
